---
title: Cannellini Bean Panzanella with Mozzarella, Cucumber, and Heirloom Tomatoes
description: Panzanella is a Tuscan-style salad that eats like a full meal. You’ve got some of the usual veggie suspects, of course—that’s cucumber and tomato here. But then there are also big croutons fashioned from baguettes, hunks of fresh mozzarella, and creamy cannellini beans. Plus a bold, garlicky dressing that gives the whole thing an added sense of gusto.
